  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Tiling Site Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities</p><p>Plan and lead a group of workers to perform the projects/works assigned by the Project Manager in accordance to approved drawings, instructions and schedule.</p><p>Assist Project Personnel to conduct site check, planning of pipe routing and generate bill of quantity of material for the project.</p><p>Advise on the required manpower, resources and responsible for all tools and equipment under his care.</p><p>Assist Project Personnel in liaising with other departments, client and vendors / subcontractors personnel on site for site coordination.</p><p>Communicating with other departments, client & vendors / subcontractors PIC on site for site coordination.</p><p>Updating of isometric drawing & hand back drawing to project personnel upon completion of project.</p><p>Proper housekeeping in workshop and work site.</p><p>Ensure that all works carried out by the workers complied with safety, rules & regulations set forth by company / customer and MOM WSHA requirements.</p><p>Update & feedback on the daily work progress.</p><p>Perform any other project related duties as & when assigned.</p><p>Able to work night shift or split shift</p><p>Willing to work on weekends and public holiday</p><p>Qualifications & Experience:</p><p>2 years working experience in Construction Engineering Industry.</p><p>Good communication and facilitation skills.</p><p>Ability to work well in a team as well as independently and demonstrate initiative and commitment.</p><p>To be available immediately or within short notice pre-requisite.</p><p>To be able to converse in English & Chinese and work effectively with Internal staff including Site Foreman, Supervisors, Engineers, Managers and Client’s representatives.</p>",
